nknown American Jewish kin networks, or their own survivor relatives. Nonetheless, the youngsters moved ahead. As Cohen demonstrates, the experiences both during and after the war shadowed their lives and relationships through adulthood, yet an identity as "survivors" eluded them for decades. Now, as the last living link to the Holocaust, the voices of Child Survivors are finally being heard.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aHolocaust survivorsxRehabilitationzUnited States. 0aHolocaust survivorszUnited StatesxAttitudes. 0aJewish orphanszUnited StatesxAttitudes. 0aJewszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 4abeth cohen. 4achild holocaust survivors. 4aconcentration camp. 4aholocaust children. 4aholocaust survivors. 4aholocaust. 4aoral history. 4apost-ww2. 4apostwar. 4asurvivors after war. 4awar aftermath. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017-2018z978311065742508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018z978311066608340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813584997423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813584997.jpg  a978-3-11-065742-5  RUP eBook-Package 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066330-3  RUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-066608-3  RUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG